args: Father, the Stolz district is under attack\nby fiends and low on manpower!\nUrgent aid is requested!
Again? What are the knights in charge\nof that blasted district even DOING?
I imagine the dispute has caused a\nshortage of knights in every district.
You mean the one with the conservatives?\nHmm, perhaps you're right—and alas,\nsuch knights are not so easily replaced.
We must endure until we can put those\nadherents who refuse change into check.
In the meantime, we've no choice but to\nhave our Paladyn somehow manage.
Ah, speak of the devil! They really have\ntheir work cut out for them.
Doesn't matter how many of you there are,\nfiends! You won't stop us!
Keep moving, Hope; our objective\nis not extermination, but rescue.
The Templars have come to save you!\nIt's all gonna be o...kay? Huh?
...We were too late. Ah, but this is\na terrible spectacle to behold.
Sentiment cannot help you now, boy.\nCompose yourself and search for survivors.
Oof, that wound looks serious.\nBetter use some healing magic...
It's not working—the wound is too deep!\nAm I really not strong enough to help?
Heal him... Heal him...\nWORK, DAMN YOU!
No, don't speak! Save your strength!
But thank you...good sir knight...\nfor easing my departure... Nnngh...
Come on, there MUST be a way\nfor me to save you!
Enough, Hope. Do not grieve overlong.\nInstead, offer your respects to a life\nwhich was called home too soon.
O unsullied soul, be taken upon the flow\nof mana and go with the favor of the\ngoddess. May you find peace in her arms.
If only I could've come sooner...\nIf only I would've been stronger!
I need to push harder if I want to save\neveryone. I must find a way to be better!
I'm going to work twice as hard\nand become five times as strong!
Enough, boy. Such impossible dreams\ndo naught but cloud your judgment.
It is folly to think one can stand against\nthe wheel of fate by will alone.
Then how am I supposed to motivate\nmyself if that's true?!

You believe strength of will to be enough
in all circumstances, yet this is not so.
A single person's spirit—no matter how
great—cannot change the world entire.

We are not omnipotent—there are places
beyond the reach of our aid, and unseen
tragedies which occur continuously at the
fringes of existence.

We can save some. But many will go
unnoticed, and even when we do find
them, we will often be unable to save
them, just like today.
Even so, an Ilian knight must wear the\nguise of hope and sally forth—including\nwhile they attend to the dead and dying.
You must embolden your pragmatic nature.\nSaving people means facing the hard fact\nthat there will be those you cannot save.

If you are to succeed as a Templar, you
must understand the harsh nature of
the world. This is the duty of all who
would fight in the name of their faith.
Are you prepared to face this reality?
But...if I just do my best...
The best effort of the greatest will still\nsometimes not be enough. This is a\ntruth you must come to understand.
Why are you saying this\nwhen I'm trying so hard?!

Because it is truth. Those without resolve
will find themselves becoming mentally
and emotionally fatigued. And once this
happens, they are forever lost.
This was the case with even the former\nHeavenwing, and it will be so with you.
He was strong. Compassionate. A nearly\nflawless hero who stood the equal with\nthe long history of the Grand Paladyns.
Yet at the end of it all, he could not stand\nthe weight of the lives he failed to save,\nand his spirit was ground into dust.
You once told me that you would use\nyour resolve and passion to see your\nway through hardship, did you not?
Having now seen the truth, do you still\nbelieve such to be the best path forward?
I don't know. I really don't. Right now,\nI feel like anything I do is futile,\nno matter how hard I try.
I once believed I could save everyone if\nI just gave it everything I had...
But now I know that even a Heavenwing\ncan't save everyone, and that's...\nWell, it's a hard thing to hear.
My dream was so shortsighted.\nSo small.
And maybe what I was trying\nto do was ultimately...pointless.
If you believe so in your heart,\nthen perhaps it truly was.
I... I honestly don't know.\nI don't know anything anymore...
